body:
It still crashes on my machine, maybe there is some environment related cause.

@JIghtuse This is how I did it:

```fish
#!/bin/fish
while true;
    echo (head -c 8 /dev/urandom | base64) >> /tmp/asd.txt;
    tail -1 /tmp/asd.txt | base64 -d;
    sleep 0.1;
end;
```

I'd like to get some more info about this crash. Would you mind running with this patch and providing the output starting with "pitch=" just before the panic? As I'm unable to repro, this would really help with putting together a proper fix.

```diff
diff --git a/font/src/ft/mod.rs b/font/src/ft/mod.rs
index c04057c..9f8fc3a 100644
--- a/font/src/ft/mod.rs
+++ b/font/src/ft/mod.rs
@@ -207,10 +207,13 @@ impl FreeTypeRasterizer {
         let buf = bitmap.buffer();
         let pitch = bitmap.pitch() as usize;
+        println!("pitch={}; rows={}; width={}; char={}", pitch, bitmap.rows(), bitmap.width(), c);
+
         let mut packed = Vec::with_capacity((bitmap.rows() * bitmap.width()) as usize);
         for i in 0..bitmap.rows() {
             let start = (i as usize) * pitch;
             let stop = start + bitmap.width() as usize;
+            println!("i={}; start={}; stop={}", i, start, stop);
             packed.extend_from_slice(&buf[start..stop]);
         }
```

Wow, pitch < width is unexpected. Here's a slightly updated patch if you wouldn't mind :grin: 

```diff
diff --git a/font/src/ft/mod.rs b/font/src/ft/mod.rs
index c04057c..6a4ea06 100644
--- a/font/src/ft/mod.rs
+++ b/font/src/ft/mod.rs
@@ -207,10 +207,13 @@ impl FreeTypeRasterizer {
         let buf = bitmap.buffer();
         let pitch = bitmap.pitch() as usize;
+        println!("pitch={}; pitch_raw={}, rows={}; width={}; char={}", pitch, bitmap.pitch(), bitmap.rows(), bitmap.width(), c);
+
         let mut packed = Vec::with_capacity((bitmap.rows() * bitmap.width()) as usize);
         for i in 0..bitmap.rows() {
             let start = (i as usize) * pitch;
             let stop = start + bitmap.width() as usize;
+            println!("i={}; start={}; stop={}", i, start, stop);
             packed.extend_from_slice(&buf[start..stop]);
         }
```
